4%''' ''159''\n|  style=\"text-align:center; background:honeyDew;\"|36.3% ''91''\n|}\n{{Hidden end}}\n\n==Education==\nWest Carroll Parish [[Public school (government funded)|public school]]s are operated by the [[West Carroll Parish School Board]]. The public school system consist of four high schools and five elementary schools that consistently rank at the top of the state in test scores and on the athletic field.\n\n==National Guard==\nThe 921ST Engineer Company (Vertical) of the [[528th Engineer Brigade]] resides in [[Oak Grove, West Carroll Parish, Louisiana|Oak Grove, Louisiana]].\n\n==Communities==\n[[Image:Map of West Carroll Parish Louisiana With Municipal Labels.PNG|thumb|200px|Map of West Carroll Parish, Louisiana With Municipal Labels]]\n\n===Towns===\n\n*[[Oak Grove, West Carroll Parish, Louisiana|Oak Grove]] (parish seat)\n\n===Villages===\n\n*[[Epps, Louisiana|Epps]]\n*[[Forest, Louisiana|Forest]]\n*[[Kilbourne, Louisiana|Kilbourne]]\n*[[Pioneer, Louisiana|Pioneer]]\n\n===Unincorporated communities===\n\n* Goodwill\n\n==Prison==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Name !! Address !! Zip !! Aged\n|-\n| [[West Carroll Parish Detention Center]] || 180 Capital Bank Dr, [[Epps, Louisiana]] || 71237 || 18+\n|}\n\n==Notable people==\n* [[Roy A. Burrell]] (born 1952), [[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]] member of the [[Louisiana House of Representatives]] for [[Caddo Parish, Louisiana|Caddo]] and [[Bossier Parish, Louisiana|Bossier]] parishes since 2004; native of West Carroll Parish<ref>{{cite web|url=http://labi.org/legislature-info/legislator-detail/burrell-roy|title=Representative Roy A. Burrell|publisher=[[Louisiana Association of Business and Industry]]|accessdate=April 29, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141017083417/http://labi.org/legislature-info/legislator-detail/burrell-roy|archivedate=October 17, 2014}}</ref>\n* [[Lee Fletcher]] (1966\u20132009), [[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]] [[Political consulting|political consultant]]\n* [[Vance McAllister]] (born January 1974), Republican candidate in [[Louisiana's 5th congressional district special election, 2013]]; in [[runoff election|runoff]] with Republican [[Louisiana State Senate|State Senator]] [[Neil Riser]] on November 16, 2013, native of West Carroll Parish; businessman in [[Monroe, Louisiana|Monroe]]\n* [[Bill Myrick]] (born 1926), [[Country music]] figure in [[Odessa, Texas|Odessa]], [[Texas]]\n* [[Spencer Myrick|W. Spencer Myrick]] (1913\u20132002), member of both houses of the [[Louisiana State Legislature]] from West Carroll Parish\n* [[J. Kelly Nix]] (born 1934), Louisiana education superintendent from 1976 to 1984\n* [[Dave L. Pearce]] (1904\u20131984), the Democratic state commissioner of agriculture from 1952 to 1956 and again from 1960 to 1976, was reared in West Carroll Parish and graduated from the former high school in Pioneer.\n* [[Tony Joe White]] (born 1943), an American [[singer-songwriter]] and guitarist best known for his 1969 hit \"[[Polk Salad Annie]]\"\n* [[Josh Bradley]] (born 1974), a former college football standout at [[Louisiana Tech University|Louisiana Tech]] and selected in 2018 as one of that program's Top 50 Players, a native and resident of West Carroll Parish.\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|United States}}\n\n*[[National Register of Historic Places listings in West Carroll Parish, Louisiana]]\n\n==References==\n{{Commons category}}\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Geographic Location\n|Centre    = West Carroll Parish, Louisiana\n|North     = [[Chicot County, Arkansas]]\n|Northeast =\n|East      = [[East Carroll Parish, Louisiana|East Carroll Parish]]\n|Southeast =\n|South     = [[Richland Parish, Louisiana|Richland Parish]]\n|Southwest =\n|West      = [[Morehouse Parish, Louisiana|Morehouse Parish]]\n|Northwest =\n}}\n\n{{West Carroll Parish, Louisiana}}\n{{Louisiana parishes}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Coord|32.79|-91.45|display=title|type:adm2nd_region:US-LA_source:UScensus1990}}\n\n[[Category:Louisiana parishes]]\n[[Category:West Carroll Parish, Louisiana| ]]\n[[Category:1877 establishments in Louisiana]]\n[[Category:Populated places established in 1877]]\n", "name_user": "Whoisjohngalt", "label": "safe", "comment": "Cleaned up usingAutoEd", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/West_Carroll_Parish,_Louisiana"}
{"title_page": "Marshall Wace", "text_new": "{{More references|date=April 2018}}\n\n{{Infobox company\n| name           = Marshall Wace\n| logo           = Marshall-wace-logo.png\n| logo_size      = 240px\n| logo_alt       = \n| type           = [[Limited liability partnership|LLP]]\n| industry       = [[Financial services]]\n| founded        = {{Start date and age|1997}}<ref name=\"NewYorkTimes2015September9StevensonAlexandra\" />\n| founders       = {{plainlist|style=text-indent:-1em; margin-left:1em;|\n* \u2022 [[Paul Marshall (financier)|Paul Marshall]]<ref name=\"NewYorkTimes2010September23\">{{cite news|title=British Minister Faces City\u2019s Wrath After Speech|url=https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2010/09/23/u-k-minister-faces-citys-wrath-after-speech/|accessdate=17 May 2019|agency=The New York Times Company|issue=DealBook|publisher=New York Times|date=23 September 2010|location=United States|language=English|url-access=subscription}}</ref><br/><small>(CIO & Chairman)</small><ref name=\"NewYorkTimes2014July16StevensonAlexandra\">{{cite news|last1=Stevenson|first1=Alexandra|last2=Goldstein|first2=Matthew|title=Some Top Money Managers Push for Fed to Start Raising Interest Rates|url=https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2014/07/16/some-top-money-managers-push-for-fed-to-start-raising-interest-rates/|accessdate=17 May 2019|agency=The New York Times Company|issue=DealBook|publisher=New York Times|date=16 July 2014|location=United States|language=English|url-access=subscription}}</ref>\n* \u2022 [[Ian Wace]]<ref name=\"NewYorkTimes2013April29WerdigierJulia\">{{cite news|last1=Werdigier|first1=Julia|title=Financiers\u2019 Charity Gala Goes the Way of Canap\u00e9s|url=https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2013/04/29/financiers-charity-gala-goes-the-way-of-canaps/|accessdate=17 May 2019|agency=The New York Times Company|issue=DealBook|publisher=New York Times|date=29 April 2013|location=United States|language=English|url-access=subscription}}</ref><br/><small>(CEO & chief risk officer)</small><ref name=\"FinancialTimes2016December9FortadoLindsay\" />\n}}\n|  location       = [[London]], [[United Kingdom]]\n|  num_employees  = \n|  products       = Investment products\n|  revenue        = \n|  operating_income=\n|  net_income     = \n|  homepage       = {{URL|www.mwam.com}}\n| aum                = [[United States Dollar|US$]] 27.1&nbsp;billion<br/>(as of June 30, 2019)<ref name=\"PensionsAndInvestments2019September16\">{{cite news|title=The largest managers of hedge funds (P&I Sep 2019)|url=https://www.pionline.com/special-report-hedge-funds/largest-managers-hedge-funds|accessdate=15 October 2019|agency=Crain Communications Inc|issue=Special Report Hedge Funds|publisher=Pensions & Investments|date=16 September 2019|location=United States|language=English|url-access=limited}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''Marshall Wace LLP''' is a [[hedge fund]] in [[London]] that was founded by [[Paul Marshall (financier)|Paul Marshall]] <ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/business/news/hedge-funds-short-selling-bank-of-england-andrew-bailey-financial-conduct-authority-a9440581.html|title=Hedge funds continue to short sell UK companies despite Bank of England calls to stop|date=2020-04-05|work=Independent|access-date=2020-04-22|language=en-GB}}</ref> and [[Ian Wace]] in 1997. Marshall is chairman and chief investment officer, and Wace is chief executive officer & chief risk officer.\n\n==Overview==\nIn 1997 Marshall and Wace launch Marshall Wace managing $50m; $25m from George Soros and $25m sourced via family and friends.<ref name=\"FinancialTimes2017April23FortadoLindsay\" />\n\nThe firm manages more than $40bn as of 2019<ref name=\"FinancialTimes2019February27FletcherLaurence\">{{cite news|last1=Fletcher|first1=Laurence|title=Hedge fund Marshall Wace hits jackpot with bets on struggling trio|url=https://www.ft.com/content/cba2c084-3a9f-11e9-b856-5404d3811663|accessdate=18 May 2019|agency=Nikkei|issue=Financial Services|publisher=Financial Times|date=27 February 2019|location=London|language=English|url-access=subscription}}</ref> and operates from fund management offices in [[London]], [[New York City|New York]]<ref name=\"NewYorkTimes2017July16\">{{cite news|title=Chiki Gupta, Brandon Brahm|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/07/16/fashion/weddings/chiki-gupta-brandon-brahm.html|accessdate=17 May 2019|agency=The New York Times Company|publisher=New York Times|date=16 July 2017|location=United States|page=ST12|language=English|url-access=subscription}}</ref> and [[Hong Kong]].<ref name=\"NewYorkTimes2015September9StevensonAlexandra\" /> The head office in London is on Sloane Street.\n\nMarshall Wace was a founder member of the [[Hedge Fund Standards Board]] (HFSB) and is a member of the Alternative Investment Management Association (AIMA).\n\nIn August 2014, Marshall Wace made \u20ac27 million from going short on the [http://www.etftrends.com/2014/08/espirito-santo-still-haunting-portugal-etf/ collapse] of the Portuguese bank Banco Espirito Santo.\n\nIn 2015 [[Kohlberg Kravis Roberts]] agreed to buy a 24.9 percent stake in Marshall Wace.<ref name=\"NewYorkTimes2015September9StevensonAlexandra\" />\n\n==Investment Approach==\nMarshall Wace manages a number of fundamental long short equity funds. The investment process for each uses [[fundamental analysis]] that seeks to identify companies which are substantially mispriced on an absolute or relative basis. Managers have the ability to shift from value to growth, from small to medium to large capitalization stocks, and switch from a net long position to a net short position. Managers can also use futures and options to hedge.\n\n==Products==\nIn addition to its fundamental long/short equity strategies, Marshall Wace runs a proprietary [[alpha capture system]] called TOPS (Trade Optimised Portfolio System), which polls the investment ideas of equity sell-side practitioners (generalists, sector specialists, strategists, and economists) around the world and uses algorithms to analyse and optimise this information into liquid equity portfolios.<ref name=\"NewYorkTimes2012July15MorgensonjulyGretchen\">{{cite news|last1=Morgensonjuly|first1=Gretchen|title=Surveys Give Big Investors an Early View From Analysts|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/07/16/business/in-surveys-hedge-funds-see-early-views-of-stock-analysts.html|accessdate=17 May 2019|agency=The New York Times Company|issue=DealBook|publisher=New York Times|date=15 July 2012|location=United States|page=A1|language=English|url-access=subscription}}</ref>\n\nMost of Marshall Wace's investors are major institutions. However, a number of its funds are [[UCITS]]-compliant vehicles.<ref name=\"NewYorkTimes2010December15AhmedAzam\">{{cite news|last1=Ahmed|first1=Azam|title=Paulson\u2019s New Highly Regulated Hedge Fund|url=https://dealbook.nytimes.com/2010/12/15/paulsons-new-highly-regulated-hedge-fund/|accessdate=17 May 2019|agency=The New York Times Company|issue=DealBook|publisher=New York Times|date=15 December 2010|location=United States|language=English|url-access=subscription}}</ref> In addition to the funds Marshall Wace runs itself, a significant proportion of the money it manages for clients resides in [[separately managed account]]s.\n\n==Assets under management==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ \n! Year !! AUM in Bil.<br />USD$\n|- \n| 1997<ref name=\"FinancialTimes2017April23FortadoLindsay\">{{cite news|last1=Fortado|first1=Lindsay|title=Sir Paul Marshall, co-founder Marshall Wace, backing Brexit|url=https://www.ft.com/content/5ab5fb78-2437-11e7-8691-d5f7e0cd0a16|accessdate=17 May 2019|agency=Nikkei|publisher=Financial Times|date=23 April 2017|language=English|url-access=subscription}}</ref> || .05\n|- \n| 2006<ref name=\"FinancialTimes2006November13MackintoshJames\">{{cite news|last1=Mackintosh|first1=James|title=Marshall Wace aims for \u20ac1.5bn listing|url=https://www.ft.com/content/f9ae939c-7363-11db-9bac-0000779e2340|accessdate=18 May 2019|agency=Nikkei|issue=Financials|publis