he [[Mar-a-Lago]] resort he owns and frequently visits.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2019/10/31/us/politics/trump-new-york-florida-primary-residence.html|title=Trump, Lifelong New Yorker, Declares Himself a Resident of Florida|last=Haberman|first=Maggie|date=October 31, 2019|work=The New York Times|access-date=December 9, 2019|language=en-US|issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/468453-trump-changes-primary-residence-to-florida|title=Trump changes primary residence to Florida|last=Axelrod|first=Tal|date=October 31, 2019|website=TheHill|language=en|access-date=December 9, 2019}}</ref>  Sources joked about the POTUS becoming Florida Man,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://slate.com/news-and-politics/2019/11/donald-trump-is-officially-florida-man.html|title=Donald Trump Is Officially a Florida Man|last=Hannon|first=Elliot|date=November 1, 2019|website=Slate Magazine|language=en|access-date=December 9, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2019-11-25/trump-now-a-florida-man-makes-home-state-center-of-campaign|website=Bloomberg|author1=Allison, Bill |author2=Parker, Mario|title=Trump, Now a Florida Man, Makes Home State Center of Campaign |date=November 25, 2019 |access-date=December 9, 2019}}</ref> including The Daily Show, which released an [[Browser extension|extension]] for [[Google Chrome]] and [[Firefox|Mozilla Firefox]] that changes all instances of Trump's name to \"Florida Man.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.foxnews.com/us/florida-man-trump-state-browser-extension|title='Florida man\u2019 browser extension pokes fun at Trump, Sunshine State|last=Darrah|first=Nicole|date=November 5, 2019|website=Fox News|language=en-US|access-date=December 9, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nThe meme has widely been seen as a confirmation of the association between Florida and bizarre or humorous activity, and it has been compared to the [[Darwin Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Holt|first1=Kris|title=\"Florida Man\" is pretty much the worst person ever|url=http://www.dailydot.com/society/florida-man-twitter-headlines-terrible/|accessdate=December 5, 2014|agency=The Daily Dot|date=February 8, 2013}}</ref> There has been backlash to the meme, with the ''[[Columbia Journalism Review]]'', calling it \"one of journalism\u2019s darkest and most lucrative cottage industries\" where \"stories tend to stand as exemplars of the mythical hyper-weirdness of the Sunshine State, but more often simply document the travails of the drug-addicted, mentally ill, and homeless.\"<ref>{{cite news|last1=Norman|first1=Bob|title=Who Is Florida Man?|url=https://www.cjr.org/business_of_news/florida-man-news.php |accessdate=November 1, 2019|agency=Columbia Journalism Review|date=May 30, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Internet phenomena]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{Twitter}}\n* [https://www.reddit.com/r/FloridaMan Florida Man] on [[Reddit]]\n* {{cite web |url= http://www.floridum.com |title= Florida Man |work= News Aggregator |url-status= dead |archive-date= May 7, 2015 |archive-url= https://web.archive.org/web/20150507074508/http://www.floridum.com/}}\n* [https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/magazine/wp/2019/07/15/feature/is-it-okay-to-laugh-at-florida-man-2/ \"Is it okay to laugh at the Florida man meme?\"] by Logan Hill, ''The Washington Post'' July 15, 2019\n\n{{Authority control}}\n[[Category:2010s in Florida]]\n[[Category:Computer-related introductions in 2013]]\n[[Category:Crime in Florida]]\n[[Category:Florida culture]]\n[[Category:Internet memes introduced in 2013]]\n[[Category:Men in Florida]]\n", "name_user": "80.233.56.52", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "(I added relevant info)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Florida_Man"}
{"title_page": "Pulwama", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{About|the municipality in India|its namesake district|Pulwama district}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Pulwama\n| settlement_type                 = City\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| pushpin_map                     = India Jammu and Kashmir#India\n| pushpin_label_position          = right\n| pushpin_map_alt                 = \n| pushpin_map_caption             = Location in Jammu and Kashmir\n| coordinates                     = {{coord|33.88|N|74.92|E|display=inline,title}}\n| subdivision_type                = India\n| subdivision_name                = {{flag|India}}\n| subdivision_type1               = [[States and territories of India| Union territory]]\n| subdivision_name1               =  [[Jammu and Kashmir (union territory)| Jammu and Kashmir]]\n| subdivision_type2               = [[List of districts of India|District]]\n| subdivision_name2               = [[Pulwama district|Pulwama]]\n| established_title               = <!-- Established -->\n| established_date                = 1979\n| City Area                       = 120km\n| named_for                       = \n| government_type                 = \n| governing_body                  = Municipal council\n| unit_pref                       = Metric\n| Municipal wards                  = 21\n| area_rank                       = 5th\n| area_total_km2                  = 1398\n| elevation_footnotes             = \n| elevation_m                     = 1630\n| population_total                = 152000\n| population_as_of                = 2016\n| population_rank                 = 5th in State\n|Telephone Code= 01933\n| population_density_km2          = auto\n| population_demonym              = Pulwamian\n| population_footnotes            = \n| demographics_type1              = Languages\n| demographics1_title1            = Official\n| demographics1_info1             = Kashmiri\n| timezone1                       = [[Indian Standard Time|IST]]\n| utc_offset1                     = +5:30\n| postal_code_type                = <!-- [[Postal Index Number|PIN]] -->\n| postal_code                     = 192301\n| registration_plate              = JK13\n| blank1_name_sec1                = [[Human sex ratio|Sex ratio]]\n| blank1_info_sec1                = 913 [[female|\u2640]]/[[male|\u2642]]\n| blank2_name_sec1                = Literacy\n| blank2_info_sec1                = 96.00%\n| blank3_name_sec1               =\n|Telephone code=01933\n| blank3_info_sec1                = {{convert|23|km|mi}}\n| blank3_name_sec2                = Distance from Srinagar\n| blank3_info_sec2                = {{convert|25|km|mi}}\n| website                         = www.pulwama.gov.in\n| footnotes                       = \n| official_name                   = \n}}\n'''Pulwama''' (known as '''Panwangam''' in antiquity,<ref name=\"Jasbir Singh\">{{cite book|url = https://books.google.com/?id=ROfsAAAAMAAJ&q=Pulwama+name&dq=Pulwama+name|author=Jasbir Singh|title=The economy of Jammu & Kashmir|publisher = Radha Krishan Anand & Co.|quote=The original name of Pulwama was Panwangam, which comprised four local namely, Malikpora, Dangerpora, Chatapora, Dalipora.|accessdate = 2010-12-02|isbn=9788188256099|year=2004}}</ref> and later as '''Pulgam'''<ref name=\"Parv\u00e9z Dew\u00e2n\">{{cite book|url = https://books.google.com/?id=LCZuAAAAMAAJ&q=Panwangam&dq=Panwangam|author=Parv\u00e9z Dew\u00e2n|title=Parv\u00e9z Dew\u00e2n's Jamm\u00fb, Kashm\u00eer, and Lad\u00e2kh: Kashm\u00eer|publisher = Manas Publications|quote=The original name of Pulwama city(from which the district takes its name) was Panwangam. Over the centuries it got shortened to Pulgam. This in turn gradually changed to Pulwama.|accessdate = 2010-12-02|isbn=9788170491798|year=2004}}</ref>) is a city and a notified area council in [[Pulwama district]], in [[India]]\u2019s northern union territory of [[Jammu and Kashmir (union territory)|Jammu and Kashmir]]. It is almost {{convert|25|km|abbr=on}} from the summer capital of [[Srinagar]]. Pulwama is often called the \"Anand of Kashmir\" (the joy, the delight), but also the \"Dudha-Kul of Kashmir\" (the milk)<ref name=pul>{{cite web|title=Pulwama|url=http://pulwama.nic.in|work=Official website of Pulwama district}}</ref> on account of its high milk production.\n\n==Geography==\nPulwama is located at {{Coord|32.88|N|74.92|E|}}.<ref>[http://www.fallingrain.com/world/IN/12/Pulwama.html Falling Rain Genomics, Inc - Pulwama]</ref> It has an average elevation of {{Convert|1630|m|abbr=on}}.\n\n==Education==\nPulwama is home to various educational institutions including\n*[[Government Degree College boys, Pulwama|Government Degree College boys  ]]\n*Islamic University Awantipora\n*AIIMS Medical College Pulwama\n*[[Womens college Pulwama]]\n*Skylark Paramedical college\n*Phoenix Paramedical College\n*District Hospital(Medical college Pulwama)\n*old district hospital\n*Dolphin paramedical college\n*KCEF law college\n*Maxwell college of education\n*Noorani paramedical college\n\n==Urban Area==\nPulwama city is divided into 35 wards making it largest muncipality in District followed by Pampore.Due to its dense congestion city has been divided into Old town and New town.Most of the government offices are located at Old town and most educational institutes are located in New town.Pulwama is home to various industrial areas such ss IGC Lassiopra,IGC Khrew and Industrial Estate Chatapora holds the states largest industries.\n\n==Demographics==\n{{pie chart\n|thumb = right\n|caption = Religion in Pulwama (2011)\n|label1 = [[Islam]]\n|value1 = 94.59\n|color1 = Green\n|label2 = [[Hinduism]]\n|value2 = 4.63\n|color2 = Orange\n|label3 = [[Sikhism]]\n|value3 = 0.34\n|color3 = Yellow\n|label4 = [[Christianity]]\n|value4 = 0.17\n|color4 = Blue\n|label5 = [[Buddhism]]\n|value5 = 0.02\n|color5 = Gold\n|label6 = [[Jainism]]\n|value6 = 0.01\n|color6 = Maroon\n|label7 = Not Stated\n|value7 = 0.24\n|color7 = Grey\n}}\n\nAccording to [[2011 Census of India]], Pulwama had a population of 152,000 of which 74,070 are males while 78,370 are females. Population of Children with age of 0-6 is 3167 which is 17.17 % of total population of Pulwama. [[Human sex ratio|Female Sex Ratio]] is of 831 against state average of 889. Moreover Child Sex Ratio in Pulwama is around 718 compared to Jammu and Kashmir state average of 862. Literacy rate of Pulwama city is 91.18 % higher than state average of 67.16 %.<ref name=\"census2011.co.in\">{{cite web|author= |url=http://www.census2011.co.in/data/town/800026-pulwama-jammu-and-kashmir.html |title=Pulwama Population Census 2011 - 2019 |work=census2011.co.in |date= |accessdate=17 February 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Religion===\nMajority of the population follows [[Islam]], which consist of 94.59% of total population of town. Other minority religions are [[Hindu]] 4.63%, [[Sikh]] 0.34%, [[Christianity]] 0.17%, [[Buddhism]] 0.02% and [[Jain]]s are 0.01%. 0.24% people not stated their religion.<ref name=\"census2011.co.in\"/>\n\n==Other cities and towns==\n* [[Anantnag]]\n* [[Budgam]]\n* [[Pampore]]\n* [[Srinagar]]\n* [[Shopian]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Municipalities of Jammu and Kashmir}}\n{{Jammu and Kashmir topics}}\n{{Municipalities of Jammu and Kashmir}}\n{{Kashmir Valley}}\n[[Category:Cities and towns in India]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=April 2018}}\n{{About|the municipality in India|its namesake district|Pulwama district}}\n{{Infobox settlement\n| name                            = Pulwama\n| settlement_type                 = City\n| image_skyline                   = \n| image_alt                       = \n| image_caption                   = \n| pushpin_map                     = India Jammu and Kashmir#India\n| pushpin_label_position          = right\n|